system.$value: BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, “Segoe UI”, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif

default.$description: Default color for text and icons, black for high contrast

subtle.$description: Secondary content such as placeholders or supportive text, slightly transparent.

inverted.$description: White color for text and icons, used on dark solid backgrounds

inverted-subtle.$description: Subtle white color for less prominent text and icons on dark backgrounds.

brand.$description: Brand color for text/icons on subtle brand backgrounds or actionable foreground elements.

brand-accent.$description: Bright green accent for emphasizing content (text, icons) on dark backgrounds.

promo.$description: For promotional content (icons, text) in the UI

on-promo.$description: For promotional content (icons, text) on top of solid promotion background

warning.$description: Dark yellow for warnings and alerts content, signaling caution

on-warning.$description: Light yellow used on warning backgrounds to enhance visibility and contrast

positive.$description: Vivid green used for positive feedback, confirmation and success messages

on-positive.$description: Contrasting green for use on positive backgrounds, ensuring contrast.

critical.$description: Red used for critical alerts and error messages.

on-critical.$description: Red used for critical alerts and error messages on solid critical backgrounds.

info.$description: Blue used for informational text and icons on solid Info backgrounds.

on-info.$description: Light blue used for informational text and icons on solid Info backgrounds.

club.$description: Highlight color for specific loyalty club content, like point totals or rewards, especially on dark backgrounds.

on-club.$description: Color for text/icons against loyalty club background, ensuring readability

disabled.$description: Grayed-out color for disabled text and icons

selected.$description: Color for selected text and icons

orange.$description: Non-semantic color. For content on light and subtle backgrounds.

on-orange.$description: Non-semantic color. For content on dark and solid backgrounds.

purple.$description: Non-semantic color. For content on light and subtle backgrounds.

on-purple.$description: Non-semantic color. For content on dark and solid backgrounds.

royal-blue.$description: Non-semantic color. For content on light and subtle backgrounds.

on-royal-blue.$description: Non-semantic color. For content on dark and solid backgrounds.

neutral.$description: Main background color for cards and containers in white

neutral-subtle.$description: Lighter shade of olive, used for secondary backgrounds where less emphasis is required

inverted.$description: Dark olive background color, used primarily for high emphasis inverted UI elements.

brand.$description: Primary brand color for high-emphasis elements like buttons and other key UI areas.

brand-accent.$description: Lime accent color for highlighting specific UI elements.

brand-subtle.$description: Subtle brand color for lower-emphasis elements like secondary buttons or chips.

promo.$description: Solid vibrant background color used for promotional high-emphasis elements

promo-subtle.$description: Subdued version for secondary promotional elements

warning.$description: Solid background color used for warnings and alerts, designed for high emphasis

warning-subtle.$description: Muted yellow suitable for secondary warning areas

positive.$description: Solid high emphasis color used for backgrounds that denote success or positive outcomes

positive-subtle.$description: Subdued green for secondary positive states

critical.$description: Solid high emphasis red background used for critical or error messages

critical-subtle.$description: Muted red used for secondary, less urgent critical warnings

info.$description: Solid blue used for high-emphasis informational backgrounds

info-subtle.$description: Light blue for less dominant, secondary informational elements

club.$description: High-emphasis color for eazleClub actions and messaging, representing loyalty. Always used to represent loyalty outside the eazleClub environment.

club-secondary.$description: Secondary fill color for elements like banners within the loyalty club page.

orange.$description: Non-semantic color. For high emphasis solid backgrounds.

orange-subtle.$description: Non-semantic color. For low emphasis subtle backgrounds.

purple.$description: Non-semantic color. For high emphasis solid backgrounds.

purple-subtle.$description: Non-semantic color. For low emphasis subtle backgrounds.

royalBlue.$description: Non-semantic color. For high emphasis solid backgrounds.

royalBlue-subtle.$description: Non-semantic color. For low emphasis subtle backgrounds.

default.$description: Main border color, used for input fields and cards

subtle.$description: Subtle border color, used for dividers and secondary outlines

inverted.$description: White border color, ideal for contrast on dark backgrounds

warning.$description: Yellow border color, used to highlight warnings or cautionary elements

positive.$description: Green border color, indicating success or positive feedback

critical.$description: Red border color, used for errors or urgent alerts

info.$description: Blue border color, for informational messages

focus.$description: Brightly colored border used to indicate focus

disabled.$description: Border color for disabled components, to indicate non-interactive elements

default.$description: Fill color used for the overall application surface, providing a neutral and calming backdrop

xs.$description: Fine adjustments in tiny inseparable elements

lg.$description: Spacing for repetitive or larger elements

xl.$description: Separating sub-sections or stacking very large elements
